  rico:scopeAndContent <https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caFonds%20consists%20of%20the%20diary%20of%20Ely%20Playter%20who%20lived%20near%20York%20in%20Upper%20Canada%20and%20later%20in%20Niagara%20County%20in%20New%20York%20State.%20Playter%20was%20a%20farmer%2C%20lay%20preacher%20and%20officer%20in%20the%20Upper%20Canada%20militia.%20In%201824%20he%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20House%20of%20Assembly.%20%20%20The%20diary%20documents%20Playter%27s%20day-to-day%20life%20from%201801%20to%201853.%20Since%20he%20was%20a%20lay%20preacher%20with%20the%20Methodist%20church%2C%20religious%20topics%20feature%20prominently.%20Other%20topics%20include%20his%20farming%20and%20lumbering%20activities%3B%20his%20difficulties%20in%20rounding%20up%20local%20militia%20men%20during%20the%20War%20of%201812%3B%20the%20fall%20of%20York%20to%20the%20Americans%20in%201813%20and%20its%20subsequent%20occupation%3B%20election%20practices%20in%20Upper%20Canada%3B%20activities%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Assembly%20of%20Upper%20Canada%3B%20and%20various%20movements%20affecting%20New%20York%20politics%20in%20the%201840s%20%28including%20the%20abolitionist%20movement%2C%20the%20temperance%20movement%2C%20the%20Locofocos%2C%20and%20the%20divisions%20in%20the%20Whig%20party%29.%20%20The%20diaries%20are%20chronological%3B%20however%2C%20numerous%20gaps%20exist.%20There%20are%20no%20entries%20for%201807-1808%20or%20from%20October%201812%20to%20April%201813%20and%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20December%201836%20there%20are%20no%20entries%20from%201834%20to%201839.> .

