  rico:isOrWasDescribedBy <https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.ca/KB/ArchivalDescriptionRecord/RG%2012-93>;
  rico:scopeAndContent <https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20operational%20and%20subject%20files%20collected%20by%20the%20General%20Counsel%20in%20his%20role%20as%20senior%20legal%20officer%20in%20the%20Ministry%2C%20responsible%20for%20advising%20the%20Minister%20and%20Deputy%20Minister%20on%20all%20legal%2C%20constitutional%2C%20and%20intergovernmental%20issues%20relating%20to%20the%20environment.%20%20Series%20includes%20correspondence%2C%20memoranda%2C%20draft%20legislation%2C%20publications%2C%20notes%2C%20news%20releases%20and%20press%20clippings.%20%20A%20major%20portion%20of%20the%20records%20deal%20with%20the%20dispute%20between%20the%20Ministry%20of%20the%20Environment%20and%20Dow%20Chemical%20Company%20over%20the%20effects%20of%20mercury%20contamination%20on%20water%20quality%20and%20human%20health%2C%20but%20other%20records%20deal%20with%20national%20and%20international%20agreements%2C%20ministry%20participation%20in%20conferences%20abroad%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Japan%2C%20and%20other%20legal%20cases%20in%20which%20the%20Ministry%20was%20involved.%20%20The%20files%20are%20predominantly%20those%20of%20Henry%20Landis%2C%20General%20Counsel%20for%20the%20Ontario%20Water%20Resources%20Commission%20and%20later%20for%20the%20Ministry%20of%20the%20Environment.> .

