  rico:scopeAndContent <https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20letters%20received%20by%20the%20Clerk%20of%20the%20Peace%20for%20York%20County%20from%20various%20officials%2C%20most%20notably%20the%20Deputy%20Attorney%20General%2C%20Assistant%20Provincial%20Secretary%2C%20Crown%20Attorneys%2C%20Sheriffs%20and%20municipal%20Clerks.%20The%20correspondence%20deals%20with%20matters%20relating%20to%20the%20Clerk%27s%20duties%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20the%20General%20Sessions%20%2F%20Justices%20of%20the%20Peace%2C%20subpoenas%2C%20naturalization%2C%20jurors%27%20and%20voters%27%20lists%2C%20returns%20of%20convictions%2C%20and%20Coroners.%20%20The%20correspondence%20is%20arranged%20by%20year%2C%20or%20portions%20thereof%2C%20and%20then%20alphabetically%20by%20name%20of%20correspondent%20and%20then%20chronologically.> .

