<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caFonds%20consists%20mainly%20of%20records%20and%20copies%20of%20records%20connected%20with%20Edward%20Merrill%27s%20legal%20practice.%20Included%20is%20correspondence%20relating%20to%20legal%20matters%2C%20and%20also%20includes%20letters%20of%20appointment%20to%20Samuel%20Merrill.%20Legal%20correspondence%20is%20that%20of%20Edward%20Merrill%20regarding%20cases%20tried%20before%20him%2C%20petitions%2C%20the%20and%20position%20of%20County%20Court%20Judges.%20Correspondence%20has%20been%20arranged%20chronologically.%20%20Fonds%20also%20includes%20various%20legal%20records%2C%20including%20affidavits%2C%20agreements%2C%20bonds%2C%20releases%20and%20elections%2C%20wills%20and%20estate%20books%2C%20and%20other%20records.%20Legal%20records%20have%20been%20arranged%20alphabetically.%20%20Also%20included%20are%20miscellaneous%20records%2C%20including%20poll%20books%20for%20elections%20in%201828%20and%201830%2C%20for%20which%20Samuel%20Merrill%20was%20Deputy%20Returning%20Officer.%20Attached%20to%20these%20books%20are%20several%20petitions%20regarding%20the%20contesting%20of%20the%20election%20of%201828.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caFonds%20consists%20of%20four%20handwritten%20survey%20journals%20kept%20by%20Hamlet%20Burritt%2C%20a%20land%20surveyor%20who%20surveyed%20the%20route%20for%20the%20Opeongo%20Colonization%20Road%2C%20from%20the%20Ottawa%20River%20to%20Lake%20Opeongo%20from%2010%20April%201851%20to%207%20April%201852.%20The%20journals%20document%20Burritt%EF%BF%BDs%20observations%20on%20camp%20life%2C%20the%20landscape%2C%20daily%20activities%2C%20weather%2C%20working%20conditions%2C%20his%20relationships%20with%20the%20crew%2C%20and%20his%20interactions%20with%20the%20locals.%20%20Three%20of%20the%20four%20journals%20were%20hand-made%20by%20Burritt%20out%20of%20lined%20school%20notebook%20paper%20and%20all%20are%20bound%20together%20with%20thread.%20Journal%203%20consists%20of%20a%20store-bought%20notebook%20with%20a%20red%20and%20blue%20marble%20cover.%20It%20also%20contains%20a%20thin%20piece%20of%20birch%20bark%20with%20some%20notes%20on%20it%20placed%20between%20two%20pages%20and%20a%20bit%20of%20blotting%20paper%20between%20other%20pages.%20%20The%20journals%20have%20been%20arranged%20numerically%20and%20chronologically.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caFonds%20consists%20of%20personal%20and%20professional%20records%20of%20Charles%20Shirreff%20and%20other%20Shirreff%20family%20members.%20Included%20are%20correspondence%2C%20land%20records%2C%20genealogical%20information%20and%20biographical%20information%20regarding%20the%20Shirreff%20family%2C%20notices%20of%20appointments%2C%20diaries%2C%20and%20other%20records.%20%20Correspondence%20includes%3A%20letters%20received%20by%20Charles%20Sherriff%20before%20his%20emigration%20from%20Scotland%3B%20letters%20regarding%20Colonel%20John%20By%3B%20letters%20detailing%20Alexander%20Shirreff%EF%BF%BDs%20expenses%20while%20exploring%20the%20land%20between%20the%20Ottawa%20River%20and%20Lake%20Huron%3B%20letters%20regarding%20the%20purchase%20of%20land%20and%20the%20purchase%20of%20the%20Bytown%20Gazette%3B%20and%20letters%20regarding%20the%20Shirreff%20family%EF%BF%BDs%20claim%20to%20the%20earldom%20of%20Stirling.%20%20Land%20records%20consist%20of%3A%20land%20grants%3B%20a%20Scottish%20property%20transfer%3B%20a%20rent%20roll%20of%20Fitzroy%20Harbour%20lots%3B%20a%20statement%20of%20property%20at%20Fitzroy%20Harbour%3B%20maps%20of%20the%20land%20by%20the%20Carp%20River%20and%20part%20of%20Fitzroy%20Township%3B%20and%20a%20plan%20of%20the%20Fitzroy%20Harbour.%20%20Genealogical%20and%20biographical%20material%20includes%20newspaper%20clippings%2C%20manuscript%20histories%20of%20the%20family%2C%20and%20a%20history%20of%20St.%20Andrew%EF%BF%BDs%20Presbyterian%20Church%20at%20Fitzroy%20Harbour.%20%20Fonds%20also%20includes%20notices%20of%20Charles%20Shirreff%EF%BF%BDs%20appointment%20as%20a%20Justice%20of%20the%20Peace%20for%20the%20Ottawa%20and%20Bathurst%20Districts%2C%20and%20of%20his%20temporary%20appointment%20as%20a%20local%20agent%20of%20the%20Canada%20Company.%20%20Diaries%20contain%20entries%20relating%20to%3A%20Ottawa%20River%20improvements%2C%20Lake%20Nipissing%20exploration%2C%20Gatineau%20timber%2C%20and%20proposed%20settlements%20in%20the%20Ottawa%20District%20and%20at%20Lake%20Nipissing.%20%20Fonds%20also%20includes%3A%20notices%20regarding%20timber%20duties%20and%20the%20construction%20of%20roads%3B%20printed%20copies%20of%20Charles%20Shirreff%EF%BF%BDs%20letter%20to%20the%20Bytown%20Gazette%20entitled%20%22Arguments%20for%20Bytown%20being%20made%20the%20Seat%20of%20the%20Government%20in%20Canada%22%3B%20wills%20and%20a%20marriage%20contract%3B%20tax%20bills%2C%20contracts%2C%20and%20property%20valuations%20of%20property%20belonging%20to%20Charles%20Shirreff%20and%20Company%2C%20Leith%3B%20and%20photographs%20of%20sites%20around%20Fitzroy%20Harbour.%20%20Fonds%20contains%20the%20following%20series%3A%20General%20Correspondence%2C%201723-1893%2C%20N.D.%20%28Series%20A%29%3B%20Land%20Records%2C%201694-%201958%20%28Series%20B%29%3B%20Genealogy%20%28Series%20C%29%3B%20Appointments%2C%201835%2C%20N.D.%20%28Series%20D%29%3B%20Diaries%2C%201831%2C%20N.D.%20%28Series%20E%29%3B%20Memoranda%20%28Series%20F%29%3B%20Ottawa-Bytown%2C%201842%2C%20N.D.%20%28Series%20G%29%3B%20Biographical%20%28Series%20H%29%3B%20Wills%20And%20Marriage%20Contract%2C%201702%2C%201853%2C%201881%20%28Series%20I%29%3B%20Scottish%20Miscellaneous%20%28Series%20J%29>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caFonds%20consists%20of%20photos%20taken%20by%20Archibald%20Robertson%20during%20the%20course%20of%20several%20journeys%20in%20northwestern%20Ontario%20between%201922-1957.%20%20Fonds%20includes%20prints%20and%20negatives%20depicting%20northern%20Ontario%20Native%20activities%2C%20bush%20aircraft%20and%20general%20terrain.%20%20Ontario%20locales%20depicted%20include%20James%20Bay%2C%20Attawapiskat%20Lake%2C%20and%20Sioux%20Lookout.%20%20Fonds%20has%20been%20arranged%20in%20three%20series%2C%20according%20to%20format%20of%20photographs.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caFonds%20consists%20of%20the%20diary%20of%20Ely%20Playter%20who%20lived%20near%20York%20in%20Upper%20Canada%20and%20later%20in%20Niagara%20County%20in%20New%20York%20State.%20Playter%20was%20a%20farmer%2C%20lay%20preacher%20and%20officer%20in%20the%20Upper%20Canada%20militia.%20In%201824%20he%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20House%20of%20Assembly.%20%20%20The%20diary%20documents%20Playter%27s%20day-to-day%20life%20from%201801%20to%201853.%20Since%20he%20was%20a%20lay%20preacher%20with%20the%20Methodist%20church%2C%20religious%20topics%20feature%20prominently.%20Other%20topics%20include%20his%20farming%20and%20lumbering%20activities%3B%20his%20difficulties%20in%20rounding%20up%20local%20militia%20men%20during%20the%20War%20of%201812%3B%20the%20fall%20of%20York%20to%20the%20Americans%20in%201813%20and%20its%20subsequent%20occupation%3B%20election%20practices%20in%20Upper%20Canada%3B%20activities%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Assembly%20of%20Upper%20Canada%3B%20and%20various%20movements%20affecting%20New%20York%20politics%20in%20the%201840s%20%28including%20the%20abolitionist%20movement%2C%20the%20temperance%20movement%2C%20the%20Locofocos%2C%20and%20the%20divisions%20in%20the%20Whig%20party%29.%20%20The%20diaries%20are%20chronological%3B%20however%2C%20numerous%20gaps%20exist.%20There%20are%20no%20entries%20for%201807-1808%20or%20from%20October%201812%20to%20April%201813%20and%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20December%201836%20there%20are%20no%20entries%20from%201834%20to%201839.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

