<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSamuel%20Merrill%20%28born%20ca.%201800%29%20was%20a%20lawyer%2C%20Registrar%20of%20the%20Surrogate%20Court%2C%20and%20Master-in-Chancery%20in%20Picton.%20His%20son%2C%20Edward%20Merrill%20%28b.%201841%29%20also%20practised%20law%20in%20Picton%2C%20and%20was%20also%20County%20Court%20Judge%20of%20Prince%20Edward.Samuel%20Merrill%20was%20educated%20at%20the%20Kingston%20Grammar%20School%2C%20and%20the%20Law%20Society%20of%20Upper%20Canada%2C%20articling%20with%20the%20Hon.%20C.A.%20Hagerman.%20He%20was%20called%20to%20the%20bar%20in%201823.%20He%20then%20became%20the%20first%20lawyer%20in%20Picton%2C%20the%20first%20Registrar%20of%20the%20Surrogate%20Court%20in%20Picton.%20He%20also%20served%20as%20Master-in-Chancery%20for%20a%20number%20of%20years.His%20son%2C%20Edward%20Merrill%2C%20was%20born%20in%20Picton%2C%20and%20was%20admitted%20as%20a%20student%20to%20the%20Law%20Society%20of%20Upper%20Canada%20in%201858.%20He%20was%20called%20to%20the%20bar%20in%201867%2C%20and%20then%20practised%20law%20with%20his%20father%20in%20Picton.%20In%201890%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20County%20Court%20Judge%20of%20Prince%20Edward%2C%20a%20position%20he%20held%20until%201904.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

