<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries> a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20largely%20of%20volumes%20containing%20registrations%20of%20births%2C%20marriages%20and%20deaths%20created%20by%20various%20Division%20Registrars%20%28who%20were%20in%20fact%20city%2C%20town%20or%20county%20clerks%29%20under%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20Vital%20Statistics%20Act.%20%20These%20records%20were%20subsequently%20transferred%20to%20the%20Registrar%20General%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%20%28e.g.%20lack%20of%20space%2C%20retirement%20of%20a%20registrar%29%20under%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20Act.%20When%20an%20individual%20went%20to%20the%20Division%20Registrar%20to%20register%20an%20event%2C%20the%20information%20was%20recorded%20in%20a%20book%20or%20register%20and%20then%20forwarded%20to%20the%20Registrar%20General.%20%20The%20registers%20themselves%2C%20along%20with%20any%20index%20books%20that%20may%20have%20been%20created%2C%20remain%20in%20the%20custody%20and%20control%20of%20the%20registrars%20and%20their%20successors%2C%20until%20such%20time%20as%20they%20are%20transferred%20to%20the%20Registrar%20General.%20%20Certain%20other%20volumes%20in%20this%20series%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20created%20before%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20Registrar%20General%2C%20but%20they%20were%20later%20transferred%20to%20the%20Registrar%20General%20under%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20Vital%20Statistics%20Act.%20%20The%20registers%20in%20this%20series%20are%20arranged%20by%20the%20year%20that%20they%20were%20acquired%20by%20the%20Archives%20of%20Ontario%2C%20and%20within%20each%20year%2C%20they%20are%20listed%20alphabetically%20by%20name%20of%20city%2C%20township%2C%20county%20or%20district.%20%20The%20registers%20themselves%20are%20arranges%20by%20various%20methods%2C%20with%20the%20two%20most%20common%20being%3A%20chronological%20by%20the%20date%20of%20registration%20of%20the%20event%3B%20and%20by%20letter%20of%20the%20alphabet%20%28i.e.%20all%20surnames%20beginning%20with%20the%20same%20letter%20are%20grouped%20together%29.%20%20Registrations%20that%20are%20chronological%20by%20date%20of%20event%20are%20most%20often%20indexed%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20volume.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20366%20prints%20in%20two%20albums%2C%20and%2094%20cellulose%20nitrate%20film%20negatives%2C%20mainly%20depicting%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Canadian%20Pacific%20Railway%27s%20Toronto-Sudbury%20line%20from%201904-1908%2C%20taken%20by%20Alexander%20Isbester%20and%20fellow%20workers.%20A%20few%20date%20from%20some%20of%20Isbester%27s%20earlier%20work%20on%20the%20Algoma%20Central%20Railway%20%281900%29%2C%20the%20Ottawa%20Northern%20and%20Western%20Railway%2C%20and%20the%20Canadian%20Pacific%20Railway%20in%20Saskatoon.%20Also%20found%20in%20the%20second%20album%20%28C%20267-2-1-2%29%20are%20photos%20from%20Isbester%27s%20later%20projects%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Grand%20Trunk%20Railway%20%281920%29%20and%20breakwater%20construction%20in%20Port%20Arthur%20%281928%29.%20%20Images%20in%20this%20series%20portray%20various%20aspects%20of%20the%20life%20and%20work%20of%20construction%20engineers%20in%20Northern%20Ontario.%20Geographic%20locations%20include%20Byng%20Inlet%2C%20Whitefish%20Creek%2C%20and%20the%20French%20River.%20There%20are%20also%20family%20photos%20of%20the%20Isbesters.%20The%20photos%20are%20grouped%20by%20location%20and%20event%2C%20but%20are%20not%20in%20alphabetical%20or%20chronological%20order.%20%20Series%20is%20divided%20into%20three%20sub-series%3A%20albums%2C%20negatives%20and%20captions%2Fcross-references.%20The%20albums%20contain%20prints%20which%20were%20numbered%20by%20James%20Isbester.%20For%20each%20numbered%20print%20there%20is%20a%20corresponding%20caption%2C%20see%20description%20for%20sub-series%20C%20267-2-3.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20however%2C%20captions%20contain%20no%20information%20about%20the%20prints.%20Cross-reference%20indexes%20indicate%20which%20prints%20have%20negatives%20and%20which%20have%20duplicates%20in%20other%20albums.%20Corresponding%20negatives%20for%20some%20of%20the%20prints%20are%20listed%20in%20sub-series%20C%20267-2-2.%20%20See%20the%20sub-series%20descriptions%20for%20further%20information%20and%20for%20item%20listings.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20Fred%20W.%20Hotson%27s%20research%20files%20on%20the%20Grumman%20CP-121%20Tracker%20aircraft%2C%20created%20and%20accumulated%20in%20the%20course%20of%20writing%20books%20on%20de%20Havilland%20Canada.%20%20Records%20include%20magazine%20articles%2C%20a%20news%20release%2C%20research%20notes%2C%20and%20photographs.%20Photographs%20depict%20the%20interior%20and%20exterior%20of%20the%20aircraft%2C%20including%20details%20of%20the%20cockpit%20and%20controls.%20Also%20included%20are%20official%20photographs%20of%20the%20100th%20Tracker%2C%20made%20for%20the%20Royal%20Canadian%20Navy.%20Several%20photographs%20show%20the%20Tracker%20in%20flight%20and%20in%20formation.%20%20Note%20that%20most%20of%20the%20photographs%20in%20this%20series%20are%20professional%20photographs%2C%20taken%20for%20public%20relations%20or%20advertising%20purposes%3B%20there%20are%20very%20few%20amateur%20snapshots%20included%20in%20this%20series.%20%20%20De%20Havilland%20Canada%20produced%20100%20Grumman%20Trackers%20under%20licence%2C%20between%201955%20and%201957.%20%20Some%20parts%20were%20manufactured%20by%20other%20Canadian%20companies%2C%20with%20the%20forward%20fuselage%20and%20cockpit%20built%20by%20de%20Havilland%20Canada.%20%20DHC%20assembled%20and%20tested%20the%20aircraft.%20%20%20The%20Tracker%20was%20an%20anti-submarine%20aircraft%2C%20and%20was%20the%20first%20Canadian-built%20aircraft%20ordered%20by%20the%20Royal%20Canadian%20Navy.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20Inspectors%27%20Annual%20Music%20Reports%20for%20Elementary%20Schools%20arranged%20alphabetically%20by%20city%2C%20county%2C%20and%20district%2C%20and%20Secondary%20School%20Annual%20Music%20Reports%20compiled%20by%20principals%20and%20arranged%20alphabetically%20by%20locality.%20The%20reports%20were%20forwarded%20to%20the%20Music%20Branch.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20National%20Executive%20records%20pertaining%20to%20the%20central%20executive%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Women%27s%20Organziation%20%28OUK%29.%20The%20Ukrainian%20Women%27s%20Organization%27s%20beginnings%20are%20closely%20tied%20to%20the%20beginnings%20of%20the%20UNF.%20Women%27s%20branches%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20War%20Veterans%27%20Association%20known%20as%20the%20Olga%20Basarab%20Women%27s%20Associations%20passed%20resolutions%20at%20the%20first%20national%20conference%20of%20the%20UNF%20in%201934%20resulting%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Women%27s%20Organization.%20%20%20The%20Ukrainian%20Women%27s%20Organization%20focussed%20on%20cultural%20and%20organization%20work.%20The%20OUK%20worked%20with%20the%20Canadian%20Red%20Cross%20and%20the%20Ukrainian%20Golden%20Cross%20during%20World%20War%20II.%20In%20the%20post-War%20period%2C%20the%20OUK%20helped%20organize%20youth%20sections%20and%20provided%20aid%20to%20new%20immigrants%20and%20refugees.%20%20The%20OUK%20formed%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20National%20Federation%20and%20the%20Ukrainian%20War%20Veterans%20Association%20providing%20assistance%20at%20executive%20and%20branch%20levels%20for%20many%20types%20of%20activities.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20Peter%20Smith%27s%20personal%20records%20relating%20to%20renovations%20to%20the%20Gypsy%20Theatre.%20The%20records%20consist%20of%20slides%20depicting%20design%20drawings.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20a%20bound%20volume%20of%20chronological%20minutes%20of%20proceedings%20of%20the%20superior%20court%20Judge%20sitting%20in%20criminal%20assizes.%20Typically%2C%20the%20superior%20court%20criminal%20assizes%20only%20dealt%20with%20serious%20offences%20such%20as%20rape%2C%20murder%2C%20perjury%20and%20so%20on.%20%20These%20minutes%20generally%20include%20names%20of%20the%20relevant%20officers%2C%20a%20list%20of%20the%20accused%20and%20charges%2C%20names%20of%20witnesses%2C%20lists%20of%20evidence%2C%20names%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Grand%20Jury%2C%20verdicts%20and%20sentences.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20administration%20files%20of%20the%20Industry%20and%20Trade%20Expansion%20Division%20and%20its%20predecessor%20divisions.%20%20The%20files%20in%20this%20series%20document%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20division%2C%20in%20particular%20the%20branches%20responsible%20for%20the%20International%20Offices%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Industry%2C%20Trade%20and%20Technology%20and%20predecessor%20ministries.%20They%20include%20records%20relating%20to%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20international%20offices%2C%20incoming%20delegations%2C%20missions%2C%20symposiums%20and%20conferences%2C%20and%20other%20trade-related%20activities.%20%20Files%20in%20this%20series%20also%20relate%20to%20administrative%20activities%20such%20as%20audits%2C%20budgeting%20plans%2C%20policy%20formulation%2C%20and%20program%20delivery.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20administrative%20records%20created%20and%2For%20maintained%20by%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Comptroller%2FGeneral%20Manager%20of%20the%20Liquor%20Control%20Board%20of%20Ontario.%20Administrative%20activities%20of%20the%20LCBO%20were%20overseen%20by%20the%20Comptroller%20from%20the%201940s%20until%201963%20when%20the%20position%20title%20was%20changed%20to%20General%20Manager.%20The%20series%20includes%20correspondence%2C%20reports%2C%20minutes%20and%20other%20administrative%20material.%20Subjects%20covered%20by%20the%20records%20include%20day-to-day%20aspects%20of%20the%20Board%27s%20operations%20such%20as%20responses%20to%20questions%20asked%20in%20the%20House%2C%20annual%20and%20financial%20reports%2C%20orders-in-council%20regarding%20employee%20appointments%2C%20price%20bulletins%2C%20and%20circulars%2C%20as%20well%20as%20correspondence%20and%20reports%20relating%20to%20liquor%20sales%2C%20warehouses%20and%20distribution.%20Documentation%20from%20various%20committees%20such%20as%20the%20Store%20Development%20Committee%20and%20Planning%20Committee%20are%20also%20included.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

