<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20newsclippings%20which%20deal%20with%20many%20difference%20aspects%20of%20Eaton%27s%3A%20from%20store%20openings%20to%20the%20cars%20owned%20by%20the%20Eaton%20family.%20%20These%20newsclippings%20were%20microfilmed%20for%20Eaton%27s%20Archives%20Office%20between%201962%20and%201967.%20%20While%20most%20of%20the%20clippings%20are%20from%20Toronto%20papers%2C%20there%20are%20some%20from%20such%20places%20as%20PEI%20and%20Manitoba.%20%20Also%20included%20are%20a%20few%20hand-typed%20press%20releases%20from%20Eaton%27s.%20%20The%20first%20three%20reels%20of%20this%20series%2C%20containing%20clippings%20from%201896%20to%201956%2C%20are%20arranged%20chronologically.%20%20The%20remaining%20twelve%20reels%20are%20arranged%20by%20subject%20and%20year.%20%20The%20date%20range%20for%20these%20clippings%20is%201905%20to%201967.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20one%20architectural%20drawing%20for%20alterations%20to%20an%20existing%20building%20owned%20by%20Mr.%20George%20Lourie%20at%2050%20Tremont%20Ave.%2C%20in%20North%20York%2C%20Ontario.%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20Architectural%20drawing%20consists%20of%20a%20site%20plan%2C%20elevations%2C%20floor%20plans%2C%20connection%20details%2C%20sections%20and%20a%20lintel%20schedule.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSeries%20consists%20of%20operational%20and%20subject%20files%20collected%20by%20the%20General%20Counsel%20in%20his%20role%20as%20senior%20legal%20officer%20in%20the%20Ministry%2C%20responsible%20for%20advising%20the%20Minister%20and%20Deputy%20Minister%20on%20all%20legal%2C%20constitutional%2C%20and%20intergovernmental%20issues%20relating%20to%20the%20environment.%20%20Series%20includes%20correspondence%2C%20memoranda%2C%20draft%20legislation%2C%20publications%2C%20notes%2C%20news%20releases%20and%20press%20clippings.%20%20A%20major%20portion%20of%20the%20records%20deal%20with%20the%20dispute%20between%20the%20Ministry%20of%20the%20Environment%20and%20Dow%20Chemical%20Company%20over%20the%20effects%20of%20mercury%20contamination%20on%20water%20quality%20and%20human%20health%2C%20but%20other%20records%20deal%20with%20national%20and%20international%20agreements%2C%20ministry%20participation%20in%20conferences%20abroad%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Japan%2C%20and%20other%20legal%20cases%20in%20which%20the%20Ministry%20was%20involved.%20%20The%20files%20are%20predominantly%20those%20of%20Henry%20Landis%2C%20General%20Counsel%20for%20the%20Ontario%20Water%20Resources%20Commission%20and%20later%20for%20the%20Ministry%20of%20the%20Environment.>
