<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caSub-series%20consists%20of%20photographs%2C%20textual%20records%2C%20perspective%20drawings%20and%20architectural%20drawings%20produced%20and%20maintained%20by%20the%20Eaton%27s%20Corporate%20Property%20Management%20Office%20from%201970%20to%201988%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Hamilton%20Eaton%20Centre%20in%20Hamilton%2C%20Ontario.%20%20Drawings%20in%20this%20sub-series%20consist%20of%2057%20original%20drawings%20of%20largely%20preliminary%20drawings%2C%20wall%20treatment%20and%20fixture%20plans.%20%20Other%20original%20drawings%20consist%20of%20perspective%20drawings%20for%20proposed%20restaurants%20and%20other%20store%20interiors.%20%20The%20copied%20architectural%20drawings%20in%20this%20sub-series%20consist%20of%20a%20set%20of%20architectural%2C%20structural%20and%20mechanical%20drawings%20by%20company%20architect%20E.%20L.%20Hankinson%2C%20signed%20and%20approved%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Labour%20.%20%20Also%20included%20are%20earlier%20block%20and%20plot%20plan%20drawings%20as%20well%20as%20later%20architectural%2C%20electrical%20and%20mechanical%20drawings%20by%20Cameron%20McIndoo.%20%20The%20photographs%20in%20this%20sub-series%20consist%20of%20photostats%20of%20architectural%20drawings.%20%20The%20textual%20records%20in%20this%20sub-series%20document%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Hamilton%20Eaton%20Centre%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20building%20of%20the%20Lloyd%20D.%20Jackson%20Square%20and%20the%20development%20of%20downtown%20Hamilton.%20%20Later%20textual%20records%20on%20both%20the%20Hamilton%20Eaton%20Centre%20and%20Lloyd%20D.%20Jackson%20Square%20contain%20expansion%20committee%20meeting%20minutes%2C%20newspaper%20clippings%20and%20other%20notes%20that%20relate%20to%20land%20and%20tenancy%20matters%20as%20well%20as%20transportation%20to%20the%20centre%20and%20possible%20future%20projects.%20%20Drawings%20related%20to%20the%20Hamilton%20Civic%20Square%20by%20architect%20Arthur%20C.F.%20Lau%20supplement%20these%20records.%20%20Records%20are%20arranged%20chronologically.>
