<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caThe%20original%20survey%20journals%20were%20likely%20purchased%20at%20auction%20or%20private%20sale%20by%20Dr.%20George%20and%20Mary%20Armstrong%20before%20the%20mid-1970s.%20Upon%20George%EF%BF%BDs%20death%20in%201981%20%28Mary%20pre-deceased%29%2C%20the%20journals%20were%20inherited%20along%20with%20their%20home%20in%20Merrickville%2C%20Ontario%20by%20George%EF%BF%BDs%20nephew%2C%20Dr.%20Gordon%20W.D.%20Armstrong%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Mary%20Florence%20%28Molly%29%20Armstrong.%20The%20journals%20were%20loaned%20by%20the%20Armstrong%EF%BF%BDs%20to%20Joan%20F.%20MacKenzie%20of%20Aylmer%2C%20Quebec%20in%20the%201970s%20for%20her%20research%20on%20the%20Opeongo%20Line%2C%20who%20in%20turn%20lent%20them%20to%20the%20Archives%20of%20Ontario%20for%20photocopying%20in%201979%20to%20form%20the%20Hamlet%20Burritt%20fonds%20%28F%201061%29.%20Gordon%20died%20in%202018%2C%20leaving%20his%20estate%20to%20Molly.%20Gordon%20and%20Molly%EF%BF%BDs%20daughter%2C%20Mary%20Jane%20Armstrong%20of%20Ottawa%2C%20Ontario%2C%20inherited%20the%20journals%20from%20her%20mother%EF%BF%BDs%20estate%20following%20her%20death%20in%20January%202021.%20Mary%20Jane%20Armstrong%20donated%20the%20original%20survey%20journals%20to%20the%20Archives%20of%20Ontario%20in%202021%20on%20behalf%20of%20her%20late%20parents.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

