<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caTwo%20creator-generated%20indexes%2C%20current%20to%201983%2C%20exist%20for%20this%20series.%20%20the%20first%2C%20found%20in%20Appendix%204%20of%20Inventory%20C%208%2C%20records%20the%20contents%20of%20each%20album%20by%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20vessel%20pictured.%20The%20album%20number%20and%20the%20relevant%20page%20numbers%20in%20the%20albums%20are%20provided.%20The%20second%20creator-generated%20index%2C%20found%20in%20Appendix%205%20of%20Inventory%20C%208%2C%20is%20arranged%20alphabetically%20by%20the%20name%20of%20the%20vessel%20%28sometimes%20listing%20a%20former%20or%20subsequent%20name%20for%20the%20vessel%20and%20the%20location%20of%20the%20photograph%29.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caUnder%20the%20Coroners%20Act%20%28Statutes%20of%20Ontario%201927%2C%20chap.%20122%29%2C%20Coroners%20in%20Ontario%20had%20the%20authority%20to%20call%20an%20inquest%20whenever%20someone%20died%20suddenly%20or%20unexpectedly%2C%20while%20an%20inmate%20in%20a%20provincial%20facility%2C%20or%20of%20an%20illness%20for%20which%20they%20were%20not%20being%20treated%20by%20a%20physician.%20%20At%20the%20inquest%2C%20a%20jury%20%28composed%20of%207%20to%2012%20people%20before%201948%3B%20afterwards%2C%20of%205%20persons%29%20heard%20testimony%20from%20witnesses%2C%20medical%20personnel%2C%20and%20police%20testimony%20about%20how%20the%20decease%20died.%20Evidence%20in%20the%20form%20of%20photographs%2C%20site%20drawings%2C%20autopsy%20reports%2C%20hospital%20records%2C%20and%20police%20reports%20were%20submitted%20to%20the%20jury%20for%20its%20consideration.%20%20The%20jury%20presented%20its%20verdict%20and%20recommendations%20for%20further%20actions%20if%20necessary.If%20the%20Coroner%20decided%20that%20the%20circumstances%20surrounding%20a%20death%20were%20not%20unusual%20and%20did%20not%20warrant%20an%20inquest%2C%20he%20was%20required%20under%20the%20Coroners%20Act%20to%20issue%20a%20report%2C%20later%20called%20%27Coroner%27s%20Statement%20to%20Bury%20the%20Body%20of%20a%20Deceased%20Persons%27.%20%20Reports%20and%20%27Statements%20to%20Bury%27%20listed%20the%20name%20of%20the%20deceased%2C%20the%20date%20and%20cause%20of%20death.%20%20A%20brief%20narrative%20was%20often%20included%20stating%20the%20medical%20condition%20at%20the%20time%20of%20death.%20%20If%20an%20autopsy%20was%20conducted%20its%20findings%20were%20stated%20on%20this%20document.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

<https://data.archives.gov.on.test.gbad.caUnder%20the%20Ontario%20Judicature%20Act%20of%201881%2C%20Local%20Masters%20of%20the%20Court%20of%20Chancery%20became%20Local%20Masters%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Local%20Masters%20were%20appointed%20by%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20in%20Council%20in%20each%20of%20the%20counties%20of%20the%20Province%20of%20Ontario%2C%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Attorney%20General.%20In%201989%2C%20legislation%20was%20passed%20which%20merged%20the%20Supreme%20and%20District%20Courts%20of%20the%20province%20and%20regionalized%20the%20court%20system.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Local%20Masters%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20were%20replaced%20with%20Local%20Masters%20of%20the%20Ontario%20Court%20%28General%20Division%29.>
  a owl:NamedIndividual .

